text: So, on this short holiday, we went to Oradea where part of my girlfriend’s family lives.
So, on this short holiday, we went to Oradea where part of my girlfriend’s family lives.
Oradea is 600 km (about 380 miles) from Bucharest, in the northwestern part of Romania, only 10 km from the border with Hungary.

It is a big city (more than 220,000 population) that lies exactly where the hills end and the Pannonia Plains begin, on the river Crisul Repede (the Fast Cris), that crosses exactly the centre of the city.
On May 6th we decided to visit N47E22.
